This is a 'helloworld.cpp' routine to test the build system.
Do the following:

1. Compile the 'helloworld.cpp'
g++ -c helloworld.cpp

2. Copy 'helloworld.o' to ../fortran/

3. Uncomment line 195 in 'glimmer_sparse_slap.F90' in order to to make a call to helloworld()

4. Do 'make'. It will return an error while trying to build 'simple_glide', something as follows:

gfortran   -I/local/netcdf-4.0.1/include  -L/local/netcdf-4.0.1/lib -o simple_glide  simple_glide.o libclimate.a libglide.a libglimmer.a SLAP_library/libslap.a    -lnetcdf  /local/BLAS/blas_LINUX.a
libglimmer.a(glimmer_sparse_slap.o): In function `__glimmer_sparse_slap__slap_solve':
glimmer_sparse_slap.F90:(.text+0x4dd): undefined reference to `helloworld_'
collect2: ld returned 1 exit status
make[2]: *** [simple_glide] Error 1
make[2]: Leaving directory `/home/hdnong/work/glimmer/src/fortran'
make[1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1
make[1]: Leaving directory `/home/hdnong/work/glimmer/src/fortran'
make: *** [all] Error 2

5. In the compile line above, replace 'gfortran' with 'g++' and add 'helloworld.o' to the line. Also add '-lgfortranbegin -lgfortran' to the line as follows:

g++   -I/local/netcdf-4.0.1/include  -L/local/netcdf-4.0.1/lib -o simple_glide  simple_glide.o helloworld.o libclimate.a libglide.a libglimmer.a SLAP_library/libslap.a    -lnetcdf  /local/BLAS/blas_LINUX.a -lgfortranbegin -lgfortran

6. To test the call to 'helloworld()', do
./simple_glide ../../example/example.config > test.out